# Append-only files: take both sides on merge instead of conflicting.
#
# Every feature branch adds a bullet under `## Unreleased`, always at the same
# offset, so N parallel PRs produce N-1 conflicts — each one resolved the same
# way (keep both) and each one costing a push and a full CI cycle. The v0.9.5
# cycle had six parallel branches and burned five rounds of this.
#
# `union` is a built-in git merge driver: on conflict it keeps both sides in
# order rather than writing markers. That is exactly right for an append-only
# log and exactly wrong for anything where the two sides might be alternatives,
# so keep this list narrow — one entry, deliberately.
#
# This does NOT remove the need to look: union can still put a bullet under the
# wrong heading if a branch introduces its own `### Added`/`### Fixed`. The
# standard headings are pre-seeded under `## Unreleased` so branches add bullets
# under existing headings instead of creating duplicates. Leave them in place
# when you cut a release.
docs/CHANGELOG.md merge=union
